  <h1>
   filename_drive
  </h1>
  This function returns the drive information of the filename.
  <h4>
   Syntax:
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml">filename_drive(fname);
</code></pre>
  <table>
   <tbody>
    <tr>
     <th>
      Argument
     </th>
     <th>
      Type
     </th>
     <th>
      Description
     </th>
    </tr>
    <tr>
     <td>
      fname
     </td>
     <td>
      <span>
       <a href="../../../../../GameMaker_Language/GML_Overview/Data_Types.htm">
        String
       </a>
      </span>
     </td>
     <td>
      The file to use.
     </td>
    </tr>
   </tbody>
  </table>
  <h4>
   Returns:
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml"><a href="../../../../../GameMaker_Language/GML_Overview/Data_Types.htm">
 String
</a></code></pre>
  <h4>
   Example:
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml">drive = filename_drive(file_find_first(working_directory + "*.doc", 0));
</code></pre>
  The above code gets the drive information (as a string) of the specified file.
 </body>
</html>